race.description: Crowne Plaza Geelong Black Pearl Stakes (L)
race.comment: BIANCELLI (15) showed good early dash and held on well to finish a long neck in second over 1000m at Pakenham. She's in a top stable and has plenty of scope for improvement. A leading jockey takes over replacing the 2kg apprentice. Draws awkwardly but the promising mare can step up and go one better. JENNI THE FOX (6) was outgraded at Pakenham but her form prior stacks right up. Missed 1L at Group level three back and she finally draws a half-decent gate. A live chance. GRACIE'S RAIN (5) was straight back into the winners' circle winning easily from the front at Caulfield. Peaks and is sure to give a big sight. HEART OF GLASS (13) missed a whisker at Caulfield before spelling and impressed. Looked a run short first-up and has won 2/4 second-up. Has to be kept onside. MISS ICELANDIC (4) peaks and didn't have the best of it at Caulfield Heath last time. She is also going well enough to consider.
